        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 1:12PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 112 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Belknap, or 11 miles west of Mosses, moving east at 50
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Deposit, Mosses, Hayneville, White Hall, Gordonville, Orrville,
Lowndesboro, Benton, Beechwood, Tyler, Old Cahaba Park, Dannelly
Reservoir, Belknap, Dallas Lake, Calhoun, Carlowville, Minter,
Farmersville, Manack, and Tilden.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for
south central Alabama.</instruction>
